cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.CV 

This paper deals with natural language processing and the robustness of NLP models to adversarial attacks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses Interval Bound Propagation (IBP) to minimize an upper bound on the worst-case loss, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper deals with adversarial attacks, which is a common topic in the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computer security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper uses datasets related to sentiment analysis and natural language inference, which are common topics in computer vision (cs.CV).
